              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Using strings as booleans in Python has unexpected results. `\"one\" and \"two\"` will return \"two\". `\"one\" or \"two\"` will return \"one\". In Python, strings are truthy, and strings with a non-zero length evaluate to True."
              },
